header.gameNote: MIDEAST REGION AT UNIVERSITY PARK PA

article.description: Penn State's suffocating D was too much for USC to handle as PSU advanced to the Sweet 16.
article.headline: Defense, Mazzante's 27 too much for South Carolina
article.linkText: Lady Lions' defense squeezes out South Carolina
article.story:
STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Kelly Mazzante scored 27 points to
lead fourth-seeded Penn State to a 77-67 victory over fifth-seeded
South Carolina in the Mideast Regional on Tuesday.

	   The Lady Lions (26-8) advance to the round of 16 and face
top-seeded Tennessee on its home court Saturday in Knoxville, Tenn.

	   South Carolina (23-8) could not handle Penn State's pressure
defense. Kelly Morrone hit a 3-pointer to bring the Gamecocks to
46-35 with 12:15 left, but that's as close as they would get until
it was too late.

	   On the next possession, Mazzante scored off her own steal to
start a 12-2 run. Tanisha Wright then stole the South Carolina
inbounds pass, feeding Mazzante for another basket. Jessica
Brungo's layup made it 58-37 with 11:58 left.

	   Wright finished with 16 points, and Brungo had 10. Jess Strom
had eight points and eight assists.

	   Jocelyn Penn, who came in as the nation's fifth-leading scorer
at 24 points a game, hit a 3-pointer with 1:25 left to start a 12-1
South Carolina run, and Morrone's 3-pointer with 6.3 seconds left
made it 77-67.

	   Penn finished with 21 points, but most of them came when the
game was out of reach. Cristina Ciocan had 14 points when she
fouled out with 7:10 left, and Petra Ujhelyi scored 11.

	   The Lady Lions held South Carolina without a field goal for
almost 8½ minutes in the first half while going on a 17-1 run.
Mazzante started the run with a layup and a fadeaway jumper, and
Wright had four baskets in a row before Jennifer Brenden hit a
jumper to make it 30-13.

	   Penn had just two points for the Gamecocks in the first half,
and Penn State led 37-23 at halftime.
